content: She presents for evaluation of her left wrist stiffness that has persisted since her left distal radius fracture in October 2023.  She was diagnosed with CRPS at the time of her injury. She has made a lot of progress since then, but she is still unable to extend her wrist enough to do a push-up. She is able to do Pilates regularly without pain or limitation, with slight modifications. She cannot extend her wrist enough to do a push up.
title: History of Present Illness

content: Incision well healing, minimal scar, excellent finger motion without painful post supination , uh , flexion to about 45 extensions to about 20 .
title: Musculoskeletal

content: X-ray of the left wrist, post-op, showed a well-healed fracture with stable hardware. Plate alignment looks good and the overall reduction looks adequate.
title: Imaging

content: Status post left distal radius fracture
title: Assessment

content: Advance activity as tolerated. Return to Pilates.  Return to clinic in 3 months.
